reviews.text: We went as 2 families - 4 adults and 3 children in total. The environment is airy with decent seating space and cleanliness. Service and food is so-so. ‘Tea water’ is charged even if you don’t buy any drinks, forcing us to order even though initially we wanted to order a few drinks only. As previously mentioned by others in their reviews, the worst is their pricing which is very expensive. We felt ‘chopped’ at the end and don’t think we’d ever recommend anyone to visit this restaurant.
Good for the open air atmosphere, friendly staffs. Food is OK la.

reviews.text:
1碗白飯HKD12元，茶資辣椒碟都要另收，最後還要10％服務費。
東西吃起來口味普通又貴，但觀光地賣的是海景跟感覺，意思意思坐著吃一下只要自己happy就好了。
在榕樹灣大街其中一間海鲜酒家，規模不大，遊客可選擇外買，或堂食嘆番一盅兩件，也提供海鮮餐，海景座位吸引人，使人留下美好回憶。
